<section id="warrnambool-goolge-map" class="section">
    <div class="container">
        <h4>Warrnambool</h4>
        <div class="row">
            <div class="span12" style="text-align:center;">
                <p>
                    Warrnambool used to be the important port during the Victorian Gold Rush.
                    Its main beach, the sandy Bathing Beach, runs in front of vast Lake Pertobe Adventure Park. Thunder Point Coastal Reserve,
                    with its rocky ocean scenery, encompasses Shelly Beach. East is Logans Beach Whale Watching Platform. Wunta Fiesta, a festival held
                    in Warrnambool over the first weekend of February annually, is one of south-west Victoria's major community festivals.
                    It incorporates a wide range of entertainment (mostly music) for all ages. The Lady Bay Lighthouse complex is on the Victorian heritage register due to its significance as an example of early colonial development.
                    The Warrnambool foreshore is a popular swimming area, and a number of caravan parks are also located in the area
                </p>
